<sect>The KDE Control Center
<p>

The KDE Control Center provides a convenient way to access all the
configuration modules. In principle, the configuration modules are
independent programs. The can be executed either by using the Settings menu,
the command line, or the Control Center.
<p>
The Control Center has the advantage that all possible modules are displayed
in a list, so it is easier to find the right configuration module.

<sect> The configuration modules
<p>

This is a list of the <it>standard</it> configuration modules provided by the
KDE base packages. Please note that there might be many more on your system
if you install additional software. You can access the help for all modules
by first selecting the module in the control center and the pressing the
help button.
